Here are other areas I’d add so you can reuse them across almost ANY app with minimal/no coding – just config:

A. Core App & Data

Database + ORM Template

Ready-made Postgres/MySQL schema + ORM setup (SQLAlchemy / Prisma / etc.)

Standard tables: users, roles, sessions, api_keys, audit_logs.

Config via .env only, no code change.

RBAC & Permissions Module

Roles: admin, owner, manager, user, etc.

Middleware/helpers to check can(view_reports), can(manage_users) etc.

JSON/YAML-based permission config so you don’t touch code.

Multi-tenancy Template (for SaaS)

Tenant-aware DB structure (tenant_id on records OR schema-per-tenant).

Middleware that picks tenant from domain/subdomain/header.

Configurable: single-tenant mode vs multi-tenant mode.

File Storage & Uploads

Prebuilt integration with S3 / Cloudinary / local storage.

Image/file upload endpoints + size/format validation.

Signed URLs + basic folder structure pattern.

B. Communication & Engagement

Notifications Hub (Email + SMS + In-app)

One place to define templates (welcome, OTP, invoice, reminder).

Pluggable providers: Resend, SendGrid, Twilio, WhatsApp (through API).

Simple function like send_notification(user_id, "WELCOME_EMAIL", data).

Template-based Email System

Store email templates in JSON/DB + handlebars/markdown.

Admin UI or config file to edit emails without touching code.

Push Notifications / Webhooks

Generic webhook sender/receiver module.

Retry logic, signing/verification, log of webhook deliveries.

C. Admin & UX

Admin Panel Template

Ready-made dashboard for users, tenants, payments, logs, feature flags.

CRUD views auto-generated from schema/config.

Settings & Feature Flags

Central settings system: app config, per-tenant config.

Feature flags: enable/disable modules per tenant or per plan.

JSON/YAML driven so you just toggle flags.

Audit Logging & Activity History

Standard pattern to log: who did what, when, from where.

UI to filter: by user, date, entity type.

Pluggable sinks: DB + optional log service (Datadog, Loki, etc.).

D. Observability & Reliability

Logging & Monitoring Template

Structured logs (JSON) with correlation IDs.

Plug-in for Sentry / OpenTelemetry / custom log collector.

Config via env: LOG_LEVEL, ENABLE_TRACING, etc.

Health Checks & Readiness Probes

/health and /ready endpoints standardised.

DB, cache, queue status included.

Ready for Kubernetes / Docker-compose deployments.

Rate Limiting & Throttling

Global + per-user + per-IP rate limits.

Configurable via YAML (e.g. 100 req/min on auth, 1000 req/min on public API).

Caching Layer (Redis / In-memory)

Wrapper for cache get/set with TTL.

Common patterns: cache user, permissions, settings, heavy queries.

Env-only config (CACHE_PROVIDER, CACHE_TTL_DEFAULT).

E. Background Work & Integrations

Background Jobs & Task Queue

Celery/Sidekiq/BullMQ / RQ template.

Common jobs: send email, generate report, sync external API.

Admin view for job status, retries, failures.

API Client Template

Standardised way to call 3rd party APIs (Stripe, Razorpay, etc.).

Retries with backoff, error wrapping, metrics.

Config: base URL + API key only.

Import/Export (CSV, Excel, JSON)

Generic module for:

Upload CSV → map columns → store to DB.

Export DB table → CSV/Excel.

Mapping rules defined in config, not code.

F. Security & Legal

Security Hardening Template

Default HTTP headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, etc.).

Brute-force protection on login.

Session & token best practices (expiry, refresh, rotation).

PII Handling & Tokenization

Generic functions to tokenize/untokenize sensitive fields (phone, email, PAN, etc.).

Config which columns are PII via YAML.

Optional: KMS integration for encryption keys.

Privacy & Legal Docs Generator

Template Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, Cookie Policy.

Variables for company name, address, DPO contact, etc.

One page to generate them for any new product.

G. Internationalisation & Localisation

i18n / L10n Template

Language files (JSON) ready: en, hi, etc.

Helpers to switch language per user/tenant.

Date/time/number formatting utilities.

H. Analytics & Reporting

Analytics & Events Tracking

Event bus for USER_SIGNED_UP, PAYMENT_SUCCESS, etc.

Pluggable sinks: database, Segment, Mixpanel, custom.

Basic reporting dashboards: signups, revenue, churn, DAU/MAU.

Subscription & Plan Management

Plans: Free, Basic, Pro, Enterprise.

Limits: number of users, projects, storage, etc.

Middleware to enforce limits based on plan.

I. Dev Experience

CI/CD Pipeline Template

GitHub Actions / GitLab CI for:

tests → build → docker image → deploy.

Env-based config only: registry URL, server IP, etc.

Local Dev Bootstrap

make dev or ./scripts/setup.sh to:

start DB, Redis, queues via docker-compose

load sample data

So any new project is ready in minutes.

